text: Marna is an unincorporated community in Faribault County, in the U.S. state of Minnesota. ==History== Marna contained a post office from 1901 until 1911. The community was named after the Marne River, in France. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Faribault County, Minnesota Category:Unincorporated communities in Minnesota
title: Marna, Minnesota
